/* ===== Legal ===== */
"legal.terms.title"              = "Terms of Service";
"legal.privacy.title"            = "Privacy Policy";
"legal.terms.body"               = "By using MadFrog VPN you agree to the following terms.\n\n1. Service\nMadFrog VPN provides encrypted VPN tunneling for personal, non-commercial use.\n\n2. Acceptable use\nYou may not use the service for illegal activity, abuse of third-party services, port scanning, spam, or any action that breaches the laws of your jurisdiction.\n\n3. Subscriptions\nPaid plans are sold through the Apple App Store and are non-recurring (one-time purchases for a fixed duration). Refunds are handled by Apple.\n\n4. Liability\nThe service is provided \"as is\" without warranty. We are not liable for interruptions, blocked traffic, or loss of data.\n\n5. Termination\nWe may suspend accounts that violate these terms. You can delete your account at any time from Settings → Account.\n\nLast updated: April 2026.";
"legal.privacy.body"             = "MadFrog VPN is built around a strict no-logs policy.\n\n1. What we store\nWe store only the minimum needed to run the service: your anonymous account identifier, your active subscription expiry, and your current VPN credentials.\n\n2. What we do NOT store\nWe do not log your traffic, visited domains, IP addresses, DNS queries, session timestamps, or any metadata tied to your usage.\n\n3. Payments\nPayments go through the Apple App Store. We never see your card data. Apple sends us a transaction identifier and the signed receipt, which we verify against Apple's servers.\n\n4. Sign in with Apple\nIf you sign in with Apple, we receive a hashed user identifier. We do not receive your real email unless you choose to share it.\n\n5. Account deletion\nYou can delete your account at any time from Settings → Account. Deletion is immediate; your credentials are revoked and the associated row is deactivated.\n\n6. Contact\nQuestions: privacy@madfrog.vpn\n\nLast updated: April 2026.";

